  "issue_title": "[Bug] Mirror path skips \u201cacceptable head branch\u201d self-merge gate when repo has no additional_acceptable_branches",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nIn `_should_skip_merged_mirror_pr`, the check that blocks internal merges where the **source branch is itself an acceptable branch** (legacy: \u201cmerging between acceptable branches not allowed\u201d) is guarded by:\n\n`if additional and pr.head_ref and is_same_repo and branch_matches_pattern(pr.head_ref, acceptable):`\n\n`additional` is only `repo_config.additional_acceptable_branches`. When that list is **empty** (the common case: repo only uses the default branch), the condition is false and **the entire head-ref gate is skipped**, even though `acceptable` still includes `pr.default_branch`.\n\nLegacy `should_skip_merged_pr` in `github_api_tools.py` does **not** require extra branches: it always builds `acceptable_branches = [default_branch] + additional_branches` and applies the head-ref pattern check whenever it is a same-repo PR.\n\nSo a PR that legacy would reject as \u201csource branch is an acceptable branch\u201d can be **accepted and scored on the mirror path** for repos with no `additional_acceptable_branches`. That is a direct scoring / incentive inconsistency between the two code paths.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Pick a `RepositoryConfig` with **empty** `additional_acceptable_branches` (or unset).\n2. Construct a same-repo merged PR where `head_ref` matches the default acceptable branch pattern (e.g. internal `main` \u2192 `main` style case legacy blocks per `should_skip_merged_pr`).\n3. Run legacy load gate: `should_skip_merged_pr` \u2192 expect skip when head is in acceptable set.\n4. Run mirror gate: `_should_skip_merged_mirror_pr` with matching `default_branch` / `head_ref` / same-repo \u2192 observe the head-ref block is **not** entered because `additional` is falsy.\n5. Observe mirror can admit the PR into scoring while legacy would drop it.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nMirror merged-PR eligibility should match legacy semantics for the head-ref / acceptable-branch anti-gaming rule: the gate should apply whenever there is a non-empty acceptable branch set (at least default branch), not only when `additional_acceptable_branches` is non-empty.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nIf `additional_acceptable_branches` is empty, mirror never evaluates the head-ref branch gate, so PRs that legacy would skip can still be scored on the mirror path.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Python version: 3.12+\n- Commit/Version: current `test`\n\n## Additional Context\n\n- Mirror gate: `gittensor/validator/oss_contributions/mirror/scoring.py` (`_should_skip_merged_mirror_pr`, head-ref block prefixed with `if additional and ...`).\n- Legacy reference: `gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py` (`should_skip_merged_pr`, head vs `acceptable_branches` without requiring `additional_branches` to be non-empty).",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-11T18:48:17Z",
